.\n\n## For each task\n\n 1. Use `create_tasks` to create task\n 2. Generate a random number between 1 and 30 and store it into a variable called randomdays\n 3. Create a date and time string variable called randomdate\n 4. Set randomdate to `get_today` output\n 5. Add randomdays days to randomdate and ensure it's in ISO 8601 UTC format\n 6. Use `update_task` to set the start date of the task to randomdate\n 7. Use `update_task` to attach workflow '65ca12f1ba5152f67913001d' to the task\n 8. Validate that you have used `update_task` to perform the previous two steps. If not, cancel the agent and output the reason as the output\n 9. Use `update_task_brief` to add a brief for each task so that it's clear for a marketer what's expected within this task.\n10. Create an appropriate image using `generate_or_edit_image` and attach to the task using `batch_upload_files_to_cmp_resource` . Ensure the image meets the following requirements:\n11. Based on the task title\n12. Not too futuristic\n13. Similar style to other images on [[url]]\n14. Choose randomly to have one or two people in\n15. Business focused\n16. Should not contain any text\n17. Use `Create_article_in_task` to create an article that adheres to the task brief.",
